@startuml
title BloSS Core - Security-Focused Sequence Diagram\nAttack Detection, Reporting, and Mitigation Flow

actor "Network Traffic" as Traffic
participant "Stalk Controller" as Stalk
participant "Flow Statistics\nManager" as FlowStats
participant "Hosts Manager" as Hosts
participant "BloSS Manager" as BloSS
participant "Pollen Encryption" as Encryption
participant "Pollen DataStore\n(IPFS)" as IPFS
participant "Pollen Blockchain" as Blockchain
participant "InfluxDB" as InfluxDB
participant "Ethereum\nSmart Contract" as Contract
participant "Other AS\n(Autonomous System)" as OtherAS

== Network Monitoring and Threat Detection ==
Traffic -> Stalk: Network packets
activate Stalk
Stalk -> FlowStats: Collect flow statistics
activate FlowStats
FlowStats -> InfluxDB: Store traffic stats
activate InfluxDB
InfluxDB --> FlowStats: Confirm storage
deactivate InfluxDB
FlowStats --> Stalk: Statistics collected
deactivate FlowStats

Stalk -> Stalk: Analyze Rx/Tx traffic\nagainst thresholds
Stalk -> Hosts: Check host status
activate Hosts
Hosts --> Stalk: Host information
deactivate Hosts

alt Traffic exceeds threshold
    Stalk -> Hosts: Mark host as attacker
    activate Hosts
    Hosts --> Stalk: Attacker marked
    deactivate Hosts
    Stalk -> Stalk: Block attacker traffic
    note right: Apply mitigation rules\nto drop malicious packets
end

deactivate Stalk

== Secure Attack Reporting ==
Stalk -> BloSS: Report attack via REST API
activate BloSS
BloSS -> Encryption: Load RSA public key
activate Encryption
Encryption -> Encryption: Read public_key.pem
Encryption --> BloSS: Public key loaded
deactivate Encryption

BloSS -> Encryption: Encrypt attack report\nwith RSA public key
activate Encryption
Encryption -> Encryption: Apply RSA encryption
Encryption --> BloSS: Encrypted report
deactivate Encryption

BloSS -> IPFS: Store encrypted report
activate IPFS
IPFS --> BloSS: IPFS hash
deactivate IPFS

BloSS -> Encryption: Load private key
activate Encryption
Encryption -> Encryption: Read private_key.pem
note right: Security concern:\nPrivate key stored on disk\nNeeds HSM/secure enclave
Encryption --> BloSS: Private key loaded
deactivate Encryption

BloSS -> Blockchain: Submit attack report transaction
activate Blockchain
Blockchain -> Blockchain: Sign transaction\nwith private key
Blockchain -> Contract: Call report_attack()\nwith IPFS hash
activate Contract
Contract -> Contract: Validate caller identity
Contract -> Contract: Store attack report\non blockchain
Contract --> Blockchain: Transaction receipt
deactivate Contract
Blockchain --> BloSS: Attack reported
deactivate Blockchain

deactivate BloSS

== Attack Information Retrieval and Decryption ==
OtherAS -> Blockchain: Query attack reports
activate Blockchain
Blockchain -> Contract: Get attack reports
activate Contract
Contract --> Blockchain: Attack report hashes
deactivate Contract
Blockchain --> OtherAS: IPFS hashes
deactivate Blockchain

OtherAS -> IPFS: Retrieve encrypted report
activate IPFS
IPFS --> OtherAS: Encrypted attack data
deactivate IPFS

OtherAS -> Encryption: Decrypt with private key
activate Encryption
Encryption -> Encryption: Apply RSA decryption
note right: Each AS must have\ncorresponding private key
Encryption --> OtherAS: Decrypted attack report
deactivate Encryption

OtherAS -> OtherAS: Analyze attack patterns
OtherAS -> OtherAS: Apply mitigation rules

== Mitigation Request Handling ==
OtherAS -> BloSS: Request mitigation via REST API
activate BloSS
BloSS -> BloSS: Authenticate request
note right: API authentication required\nto prevent unauthorized mitigation
BloSS -> Stalk: Forward mitigation request
activate Stalk
Stalk -> Hosts: Update attacker status
activate Hosts
Hosts --> Stalk: Status updated
deactivate Hosts
Stalk -> Stalk: Apply blocking rules
Stalk --> BloSS: Mitigation applied
deactivate Stalk
BloSS -> Blockchain: Mark attack as blocked
activate Blockchain
Blockchain -> Contract: Update attack status
activate Contract
Contract -> Contract: Record mitigation action
Contract --> Blockchain: Status updated
deactivate Contract
Blockchain --> BloSS: Confirmation
deactivate Blockchain
BloSS --> OtherAS: Mitigation confirmed
deactivate BloSS

== Security Monitoring ==
BloSS -> InfluxDB: Query traffic patterns
activate InfluxDB
InfluxDB --> BloSS: Historical data
deactivate InfluxDB
BloSS -> BloSS: Monitor for anomalies
note right: Continuous security monitoring\nand threat assessment

@enduml
